Specially in india the weather is so extreme while most of us do live in humid places, summers are much more suffocating and the products needs to be checked depending on how our skin is doing. Beyond the basics of skincare, going towards lighter skincare in summers is the most logical thing to do. But few additional pointers from my personal experience is 

- not using strong exfoliants, moving towards gentle exfoliants 
- using rose mist or thermal water really soothes your skin 
-sunscreen is good and everyone should apply it but using physical protection like caps, clothes etc shouldn’t be missed.

The key is emulsifying, I started emulsifying into 2-3 parts and it has helped in proper emulsification of oil cleanser which means lesser oil residue and no pore clogging and this is how I made anua oil cleanser work. 

I have realised that the sign of good cleanser is how well it emulsifies, if a oil cleanser doesn’t emulsify well it is going to clog pores. 

Some oil cleansers are really bad and leaves you with acne and clogged pores no comments on that but try using it this way and let me know how it works out for you. 

Also don’t rub oil cleansers harshly, be as gentle as possible and don’t rub it in hope of removing blackheads or oil plugs because really it doesn’t remove any ot that. 

Oil cleansers are cleansers at the end of the day, use wisely.

latestPosts.caption:
- One of the worst thing and I have been influenced by it too, looking at skincare creators having cupboard full of skincare is just peak consumerism or capatalism, it used to made me feel like they do a lot of skincare and that’s why they have this skin and may be I am not doing enough there must be something that I am missing out on, but sadly it wasn’t, everything too much is just bad, too much hydration or exfoliation.

- Not everything is for you, just sticking to what works is not bad like trust me it is not. A skincare product takes anywhere from a month to 3 months to show its full potential and you don’t need to try new skincare every month. i am skincare fanatic and I used to feel left out if something came in market and I didn’t try it, but this habit just was ruining my skin. 

- You knowing your skin is far important than anybody else understanding it, if you feel 1 product is enough for you then it is enough for you, if you feel  5 product is what your skin needs, it is your equation with your skin you know it better. 

- Showing new product everyday is just scariest part of internet, one person is showing new product everyday, trust me if someone is trying so much skincare everyday they are lying. It is not possible for your skin to take it.

After starting content creation the need to try skincare every month, made my skin so sensitive even more sensitive then it used to be.
